In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 17, 2012, as Constitution Day and Citizenship Day, and September 17 through September 23, 2012, as Constitution Week. He celebrates the 225th anniversary of the signing of the Constitution and recognizes the candidates for citizenship who will be joining the American family. He emphasizes the importance of the Constitution in guiding the progress and growth of the United States and acknowledges the contributions of immigrants in building a successful nation. President Obama encourages officials and organizations to conduct ceremonies and programs that reflect on the importance of active citizenship and reaffirm commitment to the rights and obligations of citizenship.